text: Ceroplesis nigromaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Per Olof Christopher Aurivillius in 1910. It is known from Kenya, Uganda, and Tanzania.BioLib.cz - Ceroplesis nigromaculata. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Ceroplesis Category:Beetles described in 1910
